The killer whale or orca (Orcinus orca) is a toothed whale belonging to the oceanic dolphin family, of which it is the largest member. How much do you know about orcas? Keep their home safe from dirty oil pipelines https://act.gp/2tD55Eg pic.twitter.com/afwnGz63eq

But at least we are finally learning what is killing the Killer Whales on the West Coast. Contrary to the eco-types, it might not be Alberta Oil, or tankers, or pipelines, unless it's the pipelines that carry sewage from those green people in Vancouver. http://www.focusonvictoria.ca/july-august-2018/vancouvers-role-in-the-chinook-sewage-orca-death-spiral-r10/ …

They haven’t taken an animal out of the wild since the 70’s. Most now were rescued and can’t be released, like Ty, Aku, the pilot whales. Most of the killer whales were born there. The ones born in the wild came from other parks.
It’s like if the killer whale is conscious of the bird’s level of intelligence. It doesn’t try to hide it’s intentions, it just waits there. I wonder what they think about us.
